+        "title": "Check current opentofu deployment",
+        "description": "Verify your opentofu version and configuration:
```bash
kubectl get pods -n opentofu -l app.kubernetes.io/name=opentofu
helm list -n opentofu 2>/dev/null || echo "Not installed via Helm"
```
This feature requires a working opentofu installation."
+      },
+      {
+        "title": "Review opentofu configuration",
+        "description": "Inspect the relevant opentofu configuration:
```bash
kubectl get all -n opentofu -l app.kubernetes.io/name=opentofu
kubectl get configmap -n opentofu -l app.kubernetes.io/part-of=opentofu
```
Suggest an existing issue in legacy Terraform to fix in OpenTF. 

To increase automation we struggle many times when configuring providers."
+      },
+      {
+        "title": "Apply the fix for Dynamic provider configuration assignment",
+        "description": "There is a tricky situation that I don't see discussed in [the current RFC](https://github.com/opentofu/opentofu/blob/0cc4301cd51bf3ef1de4d87edfef2ab81cb678b8/rfc/20240513-static-evaluation-providers.md). :thinking: 

Consider the following configuration:

```hcl
variable "regions" {
  type =
```yaml
provider "aws" {
  region = "eu-central-1"
  alias  = "x1"
}

provider "aws" {
  region = "eu-west-1"
  alias  = "x2"
}



resource "aws_resource" "x1" {
  provider = aws.x1
}

resource "aws_resource" "x2" {
  provider = aws.x2
}
```"
+      },
+      {
+        "title": "Verify the feature works",
+        "description": "Test that the new capability is working as expected:
```bash
kubectl get pods -n opentofu -l app.kubernetes.io/name=opentofu
kubectl get events -n opentofu --sort-by='.lastTimestamp' | tail -10
```
Confirm the feature described in "Dynamic provider configuration assignment" is functioning correctly."
+      }
